Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An agreement on the coordination of activities in 
the military sphere has been ratified today at the Belarusian 
Foreign Ministry. According to the agreement, both sides 
assumed the obligation to cooperate in the military sphere and, 
in case of a military assault on either of them, hold mutual 
consultations. The agreement also provides for joint operations 
of Belarus and Russia with regard to training military cadre, 
ensuring social and legal guarantees for servicemen, and 
preservation of the present use of the communications system 
network. The sides agreed to support military settlements on a 
reciprocal basis. 

